    :markdown
        Quickstart
        ---------------
        1. Checkout Swyp Photos git@github.com:swyp/swypPhotos.git // [swypPhotos](https://github.com/swyp/swypPhotos)
        2. pull submodules: **git submodule update -r --init**
        3. compile and try out code
        4. to get into new app: fork and checkout git@github.com:swyp/swyp.git
        ![](setupPhotos/setup1.png)
        5. Add to xcode project
        ![](setupPhotos/setup2.png) ![](setupPhotos/setup3.png) 
        6. Link Binary With Library "libswyp.a" in Build Phases; Add swyp as target dependency in project settings->targetName->Build Phases
        ![](setupPhotos/setup4.png) 
        7. Setup project linker flags to load all libSwyp class extensions
        ![](setupPhotos/setup5.png)
        8. Copy the frameworks swyp uses to your current app's project
        ![](setupPhotos/setup6.png) ![](setupPhotos/setup7.png)
        9. Add path to swyp/libswyp to project settings -> build settings -> header search paths
        ![](setupPhotos/setup8.png) 
        10. Import <libswyp/libswyp.h> wherever needed, or in Prefix to make available everywhere
        ![](setupPhotos/setup9.png)
        11. Checkout Swyp Photos project for intro to implementation!

